is past the point of no return,

2
00:00:11,167 --> 00:00:12,867
the point at which
there's not enough fuel

3
00:00:12,900 --> 00:00:14,800
to safely turn back, no matter

4
00:00:14,833 --> 00:00:17,133
what the weather is on the ice.

5
00:00:17,167 --> 00:00:18,733
It's loud back here,

6
00:00:18,767 --> 00:00:22,300
the moan of four massive
props relentless.

7
00:00:22,333 --> 00:00:24,133
I'm dressed like all of us

8
00:00:24,167 --> 00:00:25,393
who've been approved
to make this journey

9
00:00:25,400 --> 00:00:27,167
in the same regulation gear

10
00:00:27,200 --> 00:00:29,367
as required by
the National Science Foundation

11
00:00:29,400 --> 00:00:31,400
for all flights
and means of conveyance

12
00:00:31,433 --> 00:00:34,033
on the ice:
thick goose down parka

13
00:00:34,067 --> 00:00:36,167
known by one and all as Big Red,

14
00:00:36,200 --> 00:00:38,000
heavy waterproof overalls,

15
00:00:38,033 --> 00:00:39,867
inflatable buddy boots,

16
00:00:39,900 --> 00:00:42,100
gloves, long underwear, cap.

17
00:00:42,133 --> 00:00:45,100
I am talking layers.

